<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- Council tax abolished, in favour of fairer system, based on income.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Basically, the people who make more money pay more taxes..  That doesn't seem very fair.  It's like a punishment for achieving a better job or position.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- Improved rights for women.<br>
- Improved rights for homosexuals.<br>
- Improved rights for youths.<br>
- Improved rights for the elderly.<br>
- Improved rights for the disabled.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Can you clarify on how their current rights are sub par please?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- Action against crime.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I'm not seeing a contrast beeween this point via Democracy/Republic/Capitalism vs. Socialism.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- Action against racism.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again I'm not sure what Scotland's government's stance on such a topic is.  However I'm assuming since this is a high left area we're in, it'll parallel &quot;Affirmative Action&quot;, which is a horribly flawed and hypocritical ideal. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.futures-end.com" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/roshis.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alucard1515>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/28/03 6:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12841.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fun with Socialism</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Basically, the people who make more money pay more taxes.. That doesn't seem very fair. It's like a punishment for achieving a better job or position.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Is getting 5.25 (or whatever minimum wage happens to be) for an hour of hard work fair when people doing much less make an insane amount more? Is it fair to heavily tax people with little income who need that money to SURVIVE when that same amount would barely put a dent in another's savings? There's more to it than that, obviously, but it's just not as simple as you stated it either.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- Action against racism.<br>
<br>
Again I'm not sure what Scotland's government's stance on such a topic is. However I'm assuming since this is a high left area we're in, it'll parallel &quot;Affirmative Action&quot;, which is a horribly flawed and hypocritical ideal. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You should probably know what it is he's talking about before you assume. There are other ways to take action against racism.<br>
<br>
And I think some people are misunderstanding what people are trying to do when they introduce some socialist policies. They're not trying to turn our government INTO a socialist one (which hikagun keeps saying). Pure anything isn't going to work 100% effectively, so what's wrong with taking an idea from one system that works and integrating it with the current system you have? You take the bits and pieces that work, and leave the things that don't. <p><html>
