So, it's fair because you can get a different job? That isn't answering my question. I said is the wage they get fair compared to the wage of someone else doing less work? Besides, you REALLY believe that everyone has equal oppurtunity? I'm not saying that just because you have less oppurtunity that this is an excuse to give up, but you've got some unrealistic expectations about what people can do. Rags to riches isn't exactly the norm.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>should he, the man who worked so hard against all odds get the same treatment as some bum that won't work even to support his family and then demand the government give him more money?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Absolutely not, but that's not what we're talking about. We're talking about those that can't get ahead, despite their best efforst, not some lazy bastard who's in a bad situation and isn't trying to do anything about it. I realize that for a lot of people, they don't succeed because they don't try, but that isn't the case for EVERYONE.<br>
<br>
You seem to be doing what people do in all arguments; comparing the best example to the worst. Comparing the hard working success story to the lazy bum. Same thing with the other side of the argument, comparing the person born with a silver spoon in their mouth to the destitute person without an oppurtunity in the world. Sure, all those cases are valid, but there are people between those extremes, and the issue is a lot more complicated than black and white.<br>
<br>
Same thing with the homeless. Sure, some people are there because they messed up due to their own wrongs, but come on &quot;chose&quot; that path? I don't think anyone sets out to be homeless. And I'm sure once you are, it's not exactly a breeze to get back on your feet. What's he going to do? Go apply for a job dirty as hell and smelling of garbage? Okay, MAYBE you could get a job, but I doubt it'd be a good one. And minimum wage isn't exactly going to get you anywhere. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I agree that people need to work hard if they ever want to achieve success, but some people have to face extra hardships to get there. I don't think people should just be handed anything to make up for that, but they should be given a fair shot.<br>
