Me and my dad, have been talking some about the origins of the U.S. and such things. Here is an interesting thing.<br>
<br>
Taxes were voluntary until about the 1950's and late 40's, they became manditory to fund the cold war. Yet, we are no longer in a cold war, and our military strength, is exceeding by far the largest amount the U.S. had during the height of the cold war. And they were, even before 9/11, Iraq, and the name Osama Bin Laden was used at dinner.<br>
<br>
I think that if the united states survived from 1776 to 194* without manditory tax, it could do it now. You were really only taxed if you were a corporation or if you worked for one.<br>
People try to say that that would never work now, because it would kill the corporations, better the corporations than the people in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Can you imagine taking your whole paycheck, and putting it in your pocket, all your money? Man, that would be a good feeling.<br>
